tioned to the early middle ages. Translated and selected by scholar M. Shane Bjornlie, The Selected Letters gathers the most interesting evidence from the Veriae for understanding the political culture, legal structure, intellectual and religious worldviews, and social evolution during the twilight of the late-Roman state. Bjornlie's invaluable introduction discusses Cassiodorus's work in civil, legal, and financial administration, revealing his interactions with emperors, kings, bishops, military commanders, private citizens, and even criminals. Section notes introduce each letter to contextualize its themes and connection with other letters, opening a window to Cassiodorus's world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aOstrogothszItalyxHistoryvSources. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  achristian scholar.  acollection of antiquity letters.  adiplomatic letters.  aedicts.  ahigh ranking public official.  aintellectual and religious worldviews.  aking of the ostrogoths.  alate antiquity to early middle ages.  alegal documents.  alegal structure.  apolitical culture.  asixth century.  asocial evolution.  atheoderic.  atwilight of late roman state.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z978311075381308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969728zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969728423Coveruht